// Control Flow
// 1. Sequential
// 2. Conditions
// 3. Iterations
what is this?


Great question!

This comment block:


// Control Flow
// 1. Sequential
// 2. Conditions
// 3. Iterations
is a high-level overview of "Control Flow" in programming â€” basically, how your program decides what to run and when.

Letâ€™s break it down simply, especially for kids:

ğŸ§  What is Control Flow?
Control flow means the order in which your code runs.

ğŸ”¢ 1. Sequential
This is the default flow.

Code runs line by line â€” top to bottom.

Example:


console.log("Step 1");
console.log("Step 2");
console.log("Step 3");
Output:
Step 1
Step 2
Step 3

â“ 2. Conditions
This is where your code makes decisions using if, else, etc.

"If this is true, then do something."

Example:


if (age > 10) {
  console.log("Youâ€™re older than 10!");
}
ğŸ” 3. Iterations
This means repeating something using loops like for, while.

"Do this again and again until something happens."

Example:


for (let i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
  console.log("I am loop number", i);
}
ğŸ’¡ Summary
Control flow = the "roadmap" of how your program runs:

Step-by-step (sequential),

Takes turns based on questions (conditions),

Repeats when needed (iterations).

